value.value: The frenal line that is a sulcus.
The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesotrochanter.
The process that is located on the proximolateral corner of the labrum. The torma corresponds to the site of attachment for the posterior fronto-labral muscle.

label.value: third axillary sclerite of the hind wing

value.value: The third axillary sclerite that is located on the metathorax.

label.value: third axillary sclerite of the fore wing

value.value: The third axillary sclerite that is located on the mesothorax.
The spine that is located apically on the last clavomere.
A groove that is longitudinal and extends laterally on the petiole separating a dorsal and a ventral petiolar areas.
The articulation that is located between the female T9 and the first valvifer and is composed of the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer and the first valviferal fossa of the ninth tergite.
The mandibular muscle arises ventrolaterally from the anterior part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts dorsomedially on the proximal part of mandible.
The maxillary muscle that arises from the anterior region of the cranium and inserts adjacent to the cardino-stipital hinge.
The ovipositor muscle that arises from the cordate apodeme and inserts dorsally on the proximal part of the genital membrane and on the opposite cordate apodeme.
The ovipositor muscle that originates from the lateral part of female T8 and inserts on the dorsal margin of the first valvifer.
The metacoxal muscle that arises laterally from the metanotum, anterior to the site of origin of the posterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle.
The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metanotum.
The mesolaterophragmal muscle that arises from the mesonotum.
The mesocoxal muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the posterior margin of the mesocoxa.
The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesonotum.
The gland that is situated ventrally of the salivarium and empties into the salivarium.
The area that is located ventrally on the mesopectus between the mesocoxal depression and the epicnemial carina.
The process that is located anteroventrally on the petiole.
The area that is located between the malar sulcus and preorbital suture.
The carina that extends from the ventral margin of the spiracular groove to the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex.
The line that is lobgitudinal and is located  closer to the midline than to the lateral margin of the mesoscutellum.
The carina that is longitudinal and extends closer to the midline than to the lateral margin of the propodeum.
The sternite that is located medially on an abdominal sternum.
The row of setae that is located laterally at the base of the glossa.
The sclerite that is connected to the distal end of the third valvula via conjunctiva.
The area that is articulated with the right and left second valvifers at the basal articulation and bears the rhachises.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the plectrum and the stridulitrum.
The maxillar muscle that arises along the lateral margin of the posterior stipital sclerite and inserts proximally on the median wall of the stipes just proximal to the lacinal lobe.

The maxillar muscle that arises from the posterior sclerite of the stipes medial to the site of origin of the stipito-lacinial muscle and inserts on the median wall of the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the stipito-lacinial muscle.
The pleurite that located medially of the coxa and laterally of the sternum.
The area that is located between the epicnemial carina and the anterior margin of the femoral depression.
The profurcal muscle that arises form the prospinasternum.
The sulcus that is longitudinal and extends posteriorly of the first abdominal spiracle.
The impression that extends dorsally on the metapectal-propodeal complex from its anterior margin to the first abdominal spiracle.
The area that is smooth, located laterally of the frontal carina and is surrounded by sculptured regions of the upper face.
The muscle that originates from the abdominal sternum 7 and inserts on the first valvula.
The row of setae that is located on the fore wing.
The notch that is located on the margin of sawtooth.

label.value: sensillar patch of the second valvifer

value.value: The patch that is composed of placoid sensilla adjacent to the intervalvifer articulation.
The ovipositor muscle that arises anteriorly from the dorsal flange of the second valvifer and inserts anteriorly on the dorsal part of the genital membrane.

label.value: second axillary sclerite of the fore wing

value.value: The second axillary sclerite  that is located on the mesothorax.
The abdominal muscle that inserts on the second abdominal tergum.
The abdominal muscle that inserts on the second abdominal sternum.
The area that is located on the alinotum and is situated anterior to the scutoscutellar suture.
The process that is located just medially of the margin of the scutellar plate.

label.value: glandular release pit of the scutellum

value.value: The area that is concave is located medially on the scutellar plate and corresponds to the opening of an exocrine gland.
The sulcus that extends dorsomedially from the upper median margin of the antennal rim.
The area that is set off from the lateral area of the mesoscutum by the anteriorly extended dorsal axillar area.
